events.name: Buffalo Bills at Houston Texans

headlines.description: Deshaun Watson threw a touchdown pass and ran for a score in regulation and then led the winning drive in overtime as the Texans added another comeback to Houston playoff history by rallying from a double-digit second-half deficit for a 22-19 victory...
headlines.shortLinkText: Texans roar past Bills for 22-19 win in OT

events.name: Tennessee Titans at New England Patriots

headlines.description: Derrick Henry rushed for 182 yards and a touchdown while Tennessee's defense stymied Tom Brady and perhaps ended his championship-filled New England career with a 20-13 wild-card victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Derrick Henry, Titans stun Patriots 20-13 in wild-card upset

events.name: Minnesota Vikings at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: Kirk Cousins hit tight end Kyle Rudolph with a 4-yard fade on third-and-goal in overtime, and the Minnesota Vikings pulled out a 26-20 victory over the Saints in the wild-card round of the NFC playoffs on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cook, Vikings upend Saints 26-20 in OT in NFC playoffs

events.name: Seattle Seahawks at Philadelphia Eagles

headlines.description: After Jadeveon Clowney knocked out Carson Wentz, Russell Wilson and the Seattle Seahawks knocked off the Philadelphia Eagles.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson leads Seahawks past Eagles 17-9

events.name: Minnesota Vikings at San Francisco 49ers

headlines.description: Jimmy Garoppolo threw a TD pass  on his opening drive as a playoff starter and then watched San Francisco's defense and running game take over from there in the 49ers' 27-10 victory over the Minnesota Vikings in the divisional round Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: 49ers win 1st playoff game in 6 years, 27-10 over Vikings

events.name: Tennessee Titans at Baltimore Ravens

headlines.description: The Tennessee Titans fear no one. Not even the NFL's best team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Titans stun Ravens, head to AFC title game with 28-12 win

events.name: Houston Texans at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: The Kansas City Chiefs are back in the AFC championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chiefs rally from 24-0 hole to beat Texans 51-31 in playoffs

events.name: Seattle Seahawks at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: Aaron Rodgers connected with Davante Adams eight times for 160 yards and two touchdowns, Green Bay's spruced-up defense fended off a spirited Seattle rally, and the Packers held on for a 28-23 victory Sunday night to reach the NFC championship game...
headlines.shortLinkText: Packers hold off Seahawks 28-23 to reach NFC title game

events.name: Tennessee Titans at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: Patrick Mahomes tip-toed down the sideline for a game-turning touchdown, added three TD passes, and the Kansas City Chiefs made their first Super Bowl in a half-century by beating the Tennessee Titans 35-24 Sunday for the AFC championship.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes' feet, arms, lift Chiefs to Super Bowl over Titans

events.name: Green Bay Packers at San Francisco 49ers

headlines.description: Raheem Mostert rushed for 220 yards and four touchdowns  to make quarterback Jimmy Garoppolo mostly a spectator, Nick Bosa harassed Aaron Rodgers from the start and the San Francisco 49ers beat the Green Bay Packers 37-20 for the NFC championship on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mostert lifts 49ers to Super Bowl with 37-20 win vs Packers

events.name: NFC All-Stars at AFC All-Stars

headlines.description: The Pro Bowl turned into a Kobe Bryant tribute.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kobe Bryant remembered as AFC beats NFC again in Pro Bowl

events.name: San Francisco 49ers at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: Patrick Mahomes led Kansas City to three touchdowns in the final 6:13, and the Chiefs overcame a double-digit deficit for the third postseason game in a row to beat the San Francisco 49ers 31-20 Sunday in the Super Bowl.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes leads Chiefs' rally past 49ers in Super Bowl, 31-20

events.name: Houston Texans at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: Russell Wilson was cooking right from the start, throwing four touchdown passes to lead the Seattle Seahawks to a 38-25 victory over the Atlanta Falcons in the season opener Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson throws 4 TD passes, Seahawks beat Falcons 38-25

events.name: New York Jets at Buffalo Bills

headlines.description: Josh Allen led three consecutive first-half touchdown drives, and the Buffalo Bills overcame their own sloppiness and injuries to two starting linebackers in a 27-17 season-opening win over the New York Jets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen tops 300 yards passing in Bills' 27-17 win over Jets

events.name: Chicago Bears at Detroit Lions

headlines.description: Mitchell Trubisky perfectly lofted a 27-yard go-ahead touchdown pass to Anthony Miller with 1:54 remaining and the Chicago Bears held on to beat the Detroit Lions 27-23 Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trubisky throws 3 TDs in 4th to help Bears beat Lions 27-23

events.name: Green Bay Packers at Minnesota Vikings

headlines.description: Aaron Rodgers took full advantage of the young cornerbacks and the empty stadium in Minnesota, beginning his 13th season as Green Bay's starting quarterback by passing for 364 yards and four touchdowns to lead the Packers past the Vikings 43-34 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Rodgers at ease as Packers roll past Vikings 43-34

events.name: Miami Dolphins at New England Patriots

headlines.description: Cam Newton looked just fine as Tom Brady's replacement, rushing for two touchdowns Sunday, and the New England Patriots beat the Miami Dolphins 21-11 to open the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Newton runs for 2 TDs, Patriots hold off Dolphins 21-11

events.name: Philadelphia Eagles at Washington

headlines.description: The Washington Football Team played like a group of guys determined to make a name for themselves.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington gets 8 sacks, rallies for 27-17 win over Eagles

events.name: Las Vegas Raiders at Carolina Panthers

headlines.description: Josh Jacobs ran for 93 yards and three touchdowns, Derek Carr threw for 239 yards and a score and the Las Vegas Raiders hung on to beat the Carolina Panthers 34-30 on Sunday to spoil Matt Rhule's coaching debut.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jacobs runs for 3 TDs as Raiders hold off Panthers 34-30

events.name: Indianapolis Colts at Jacksonville Jaguars

headlines.description: Minshew Mania is back and maybe better than before.
headlines.shortLinkText: Minshew Mania 2.0: Jaguars stun Colts 27-20 in season opener

events.name: Cleveland Browns at Baltimore Ravens

headlines.description: Looking every bit like the reigning NFL MVP, Lamar Jackson threw for 275 yards and three touchdowns to help the Baltimore Ravens beat the Browns 38-6 Sunday, ruining Kevin Stefanski's debut as Cleveland's head coach in a game played without fans in...

events.name: Los Angeles Chargers at Cincinnati Bengals

headlines.description: Heisman winner Joe Burrow ran 23 yards untouched for a touchdown -- the best moment of his NFL debut -- but the Los Angeles Chargers roughed him up and rallied for a 16-13 victory Sunday over the Cincinnati Bengals.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burrow runs for TD but Chargers rally 16-13 over Bengals

events.name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: Tom Brady was intercepted twice in his Tampa Bay debut, Alvin Kamara scored touchdowns running and receiving, and the New Orleans Saints beat the Buccaneers 34-23 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Saints intercept Brady twice in 34-23 win over Bucs

events.name: Arizona Cardinals at San Francisco 49ers

headlines.description: DeAndre Hopkins had a career-high 14 catches for 151 yards in his Arizona debut and set up Kenyan Drake's 1-yard TD run with 5:03 to play that led the Cardinals over the San Francisco 49ers 24-20 on Sunday.

headlines.description: Malcolm Brown rushed for a career-high 79 yards and two touchdowns, Jared Goff passed for 275 yards and the Los Angeles Rams opened SoFi Stadium with a 20-17 victory over the Dallas Cowboys on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rams open SoFi Stadium in style with 20-17 win over Cowboys

events.name: Pittsburgh Steelers at New York Giants

headlines.description: Ben Roethlisberger did a very Pittsburgh thing in his return to the lineup, riding the Steelers' defense and running game to victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Defense, Snell, Big Ben carry Pittsburgh over Giants 26-16

events.name: Tennessee Titans at Denver Broncos

headlines.description: New kicker Stephen Gostkowski avoided a disastrous debut with the Tennessee Titans in the nick of time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gostkowski finally delivers in Titans' 16-14 win at Denver

events.name: Cincinnati Bengals at Cleveland Browns
New York Giants at Chicago Bears

headlines.description: Mitchell Trubisky threw two touchdown passes and the Chicago Bears hung on to beat the New York Giants 17-13 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trubisky 2 TD passes, Barkley hurt as Bears edge Giants

events.name: Atlanta Falcons at Dallas Cowboys

headlines.description: Greg Zuerlein kicked a 46-yard field goal as time expired, and the Dallas Cowboys overcame four fumbles and a 20-point deficit in the first quarter to beat the Atlanta Falcons 40-39 in coach Mike McCarthy's home debut Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cowboys' rally stuns Falcons 40-39 in McCarthy's home debut

events.name: Detroit Lions at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: Aaron Jones rushed for a career-high 168 yards and scored three touchdowns, including a 75-yard breakaway, as the Green Bay Packers rallied from an early 11-point deficit to beat the Detroit Lions 42-21 on Sunday.

events.name: Jacksonville Jaguars at Tennessee Titans

headlines.description: Stephen Gostkowski kicked a 49-yard field goal with 1:36 left, and the Tennessee Titans remain undefeated after holding off the Jacksonville Jaguars 33-30 Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gostkowski kicks 49-yarder as Titans beat Jaguars 33-30

events.name: Minnesota Vikings at Indianapolis Colts

headlines.description: Jonathan Taylor looked right at home in his first NFL start.
headlines.shortLinkText: Taylor makes hefty workload pay off as Colts beat Vikings

events.name: Buffalo Bills at Miami Dolphins

headlines.description: Josh Allen threw for 417 yards and four touchdowns, both career highs, and the Buffalo Bills beat AFC East rival Miami for the fourth consecutive time Sunday, 31-28.

events.name: San Francisco 49ers at New York Jets
Los Angeles Rams at Philadelphia Eagles

headlines.shortLinkText: Goff tosses 3 TD passes to Higbee, Rams beat Eagles 37-19

headlines.shortLinkText: Steelers knock out Lock, hold off Driskel, Broncos 26-21

events.name: Carolina Panthers at Tampa Bay Buccaneers

headlines.description: Tom Brady got his first win with the Tampa Bay Buccaneers on Sunday, throwing for 217 yards, one touchdown and an interception in a 31-17 victory over the Carolina Panthers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brady, Fournette lead Bucs over Panthers 31-17

events.name: Washington  at Arizona Cardinals

headlines.description: Kyler Murray threw for 286 yards and a touchdown and ran for two more scores to lead the Arizona Cardinals over the Washington Football Team 30-15 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray runs for 2 TDs, Cardinals roll past Washington 30-15

events.name: Kansas City Chiefs at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.shortLinkText: Butker good from 58 in OT, Chiefs survive Herbert's LA debut

events.name: Baltimore Ravens at Houston Texans

headlines.description: Lamar Jackson threw a touchdown pass, Mark Ingram ran for a TD and the Baltimore Ravens added a score on defense to to beat the mistake-prone Houston Texans 33-16 on Sunday.

headlines.shortLinkText: Seahawks stuff Newton on final play, beat Patriots 35-30

events.name: New Orleans Saints at Las Vegas Raiders

headlines.shortLinkText: Fitzpatrick handles Jaguars again, this time with Dolphins

headlines.shortLinkText: Another Falcons collapse: Foles' 3 TDs lead 30-26 Bears win

events.name: Los Angeles Rams at Buffalo Bills

headlines.description: Josh Allen completed a 3-yard touchdown pass to tight Tyler Kroft with 15 seconds remaining, and the Buffalo Bills survived to beat the Los Angeles Rams 35-32 after squandering a 25-point lead on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bills rally to beat Rams 35-32 after blowing 25-point lead

events.name: Washington  at Cleveland Browns
Tennessee Titans at Minnesota Vikings

headlines.description: Stephen Gostkowski made his career-high sixth field goal of game, a 55-yarder with 1:48 left that lifted undefeated Tennessee to a 31-30 victory over the Minnesota Vikings on Sunday after Derrick Henry and Ryan Tannehill carried the Titans on another...
headlines.shortLinkText: Titans top winless Vikes 31-30; Gostkowski has 6 FGs

events.name: Las Vegas Raiders at New England Patriots

headlines.description: Rex Burkhead scored three touchdowns and Bill Belichick became the third coach in NFL history to reach 275 regular-season victories in the New England Patriots' 36-20 win over the Las Vegas Raiders on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burkhead's 3 TDs power Patriots to 36-20 win over Raiders

events.name: San Francisco 49ers at New York Giants

headlines.shortLinkText: Banged up 49ers win again at MetLife, beat winless Giants

events.name: Cincinnati Bengals at Philadelphia Eagles

headlines.description: Joe Burrow kept his team from losing again. So did Carson Wentz after several mistakes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bengals, Eagles play to 23-23 tie

events.name: Houston Texans at Pittsburgh Steelers

headlines.description: James Conner ran for 109 yards and the go-ahead touchdown midway through the fourth quarter as the Pittsburgh Steelers stayed perfect by rallying past the Houston Texans 28-21 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Steelers stay perfect, keep Texans winless in 28-21 victory

events.name: New York Jets at Indianapolis Colts
Carolina Panthers at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: Carolina's defense forced three Los Angeles turnovers, Joey Slye kicked five field goals and the Panthers beat the Chargers 21-16 on Sunday, giving coach Matt Rhule his first NFL victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Panthers beat Chargers 21-16 for Rhule's first NFL victory

events.name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Denver Broncos

headlines.shortLinkText: Brady, Barrett lead Buccaneers past  Broncos 28-10

events.name: Detroit Lions at Arizona Cardinals

headlines.shortLinkText: Lions snap 11-game losing streak, beat Cardinals 26-23

events.name: Dallas Cowboys at Seattle Seahawks

events.name: Green Bay Packers at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: Aaron Rodgers passed for 283 yards and three touchdowns, and the Green Bay Packers remained unbeaten with a 37-30 victory over the New Orleans Saints on Sunday night.

headlines.shortLinkText: Mixon's 3 TDs pace Bengals in 33-25 win over Jaguars

headlines.description: Baker Mayfield and Myles Garrett each had a homecoming gift waiting when Cleveland visited Dallas in their home state Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mayfield, Garrett right at home as Browns beat Cowboys 49-38

events.name: New Orleans Saints at Detroit Lions

headlines.description: Drew Brees threw two touchdown passes to Tre'Quan Smith 2:19 apart in the second quarter, helping the short-handed New Orleans Saints overcome a 14-point deficit and beat the Detroit Lions 35-29 Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Saints score 5 straight TDs in 35-29 win over Lions

events.name: Seattle Seahawks at Miami Dolphins
Los Angeles Chargers at Tampa Bay Buccaneers

headlines.description: Tom Brady threw for 369 yards and five touchdowns, all to different receivers, helping the Tampa Bay Buccaneers rally from a 17-point deficit Sunday to beat the Los Angeles Chargers 38-31 for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brady throws for 5 TDs, Bucs rally to beat Chargers 38-31

events.name: Baltimore Ravens at Washington

headlines.description: Lamar Jackson ran for a 50-yard touchdown and threw for two scores in a bounce-back performance by the reigning NFL MVP and the Baltimore Ravens, who took control early against Washington in a 31-17 victory Sunday.

events.name: Arizona Cardinals at Carolina Panthers

headlines.description: Teddy Bridgewater threw for 276 yards and two touchdowns, ran for his first score since a devastating knee injury in 2016, and the Carolina Panthers solved their red zone woes in a 31-21 win over the Arizona Cardinals on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridgewater, Panthers fix red-zone woes, top Cardinals 31-21

headlines.description: Dalvin Cook ran for 130 yards and two touchdowns and the Minnesota Vikings withstood a late rally from the winless Houston Texans to get their first victory on Sunday, 31-23.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cook has 2 TDs as Vikings get 1st win, 31-23 over Texans

events.name: New York Giants at Los Angeles Rams

headlines.description: Jared Goff hit Cooper Kupp for a 55-yard touchdown with 6:56 to play, and the Los Angeles Rams grinded out a 17-9 victory over the New York Giants on Sunday in a game marred by a postgame fight between Rams cornerback Jalen Ramsey and Giants receiver...

headlines.description: — Houston coach Lovie Smith kept insisting his team would play for the win Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texans rally for 32-31 win at Indy but lose top draft pick

events.name: Buffalo Bills at Las Vegas Raiders

headlines.description: Shaking off a banged-up left shoulder, Josh Allen threw for two touchdowns and rushed for another, leading the Buffalo Bills to a 30-23 victory over the Las Vegas Raiders on Sunday.
